Discord: Imagine a Place
Discord: Imagine a Place
Imagine a human website.=C2=A0
Imagine a place where dank memes flow like honey.
Imagine a place where potatoes thrive.=C2=A0
Imagine a place where humans and bots live in harmony.=C2=A0
Imagine, in other words, a place like Discord.=C2=A0
As part of it=E2=80=99s latest ad campaign, Discord asked users to describe=
 the chat platform to someone who had never used it before. It=E2=80=99s a =
testament to the company=E2=80=99s customer love and broad usage that the r=
esults read like dispatches from an unknown and invisible realm; Lucy and E=
dmund trying to explain Narnia, Harry relaying the magic of the wizarding w=
orld, Neo stumbling through a depiction of the The Matrix.=C2=A0
Imagine a closet that opens onto a kingdom of talking animals.=C2=A0
Imagine running through a wall to find your new school.=C2=A0
Imagine a pill that melts reality.=C2=A0
The fact that these work just as well for Discord as the official entries t=
ells us something subtly profound. Discord is not just a communication plat=
form, it=E2=80=99s a hidden world.=C2=A0
While Mark Zuckerberg believes he is best placed to homestead the metaverse=
, he may be surprised to find a thriving, indigenous species has already ta=
ken hold: Discord. More than any other business, the company is truly =E2=
=80=9Cmetaverse native,=E2=80=9D unwittingly built for the future. First de=
signed for gamers =E2=80=94 the metaverse=E2=80=99s pioneers =E2=80=94 time=
 has allowed it to flourish on adjacent plots. Educational groups, investin=
g communities, and avid fandoms rely on Discord=E2=80=99s service to commun=
e and converse.
Of course, it has also become the platform of choice for the many new entit=
ies, from protocols to NFT projects to DAOs, building in the lustrous, inch=
oate world of web3.=C2=A0
Yet the fact that Discord is best described in such rich, intricate metapho=
r is also an indication that its identity has not settled. Unlike almost an=
y other social business, Discord feels fluid, biotic, an organism that has =
yet to fully evolve. Though the company has succeeded in securing a $15 bil=
lion valuation and earns hundreds of millions in revenue, there=E2=80=99s t=
he sense that its current manifestation is perhaps only halfway to its end =
state. For Discord to reach its obscene potential, CEO Jason Citron =E2=80=
=8B=E2=80=94 no stranger to pivots =E2=80=94 may have to embrace new techno=
logies, consider different revenue streams, and lean into the novel paradig=
ms of web3.=C2=A0
Discord has the chance to be the metaverse=E2=80=99s natural social infrast=
ructure. That is a prize potentially so large that attempts to quantify it =
risk being off base by several orders of magnitude.=C2=A0
To build such a consequential business, Discord will need more than imagina=
tion. In today=E2=80=99s piece, we=E2=80=99ll be sliding into Discord=E2=80=
=99s DMs to unpack different facets of the company. That includes:=C2=A0
