nd false starts than almost any other business.=C2=A0
A dizzying product. Discord can be hard to understand, especially for aged =
millennials like Packy and me. We do our best to dissect the chaos of Disco=
rd=E2=80=99s chat.=C2=A0
A forking user base. Though it began as a tool for gamers, Discord is now w=
idely used. We=E2=80=99ll talk about its primary constituencies.=C2=A0
Slow monetization. While it has grown rapidly, Discord=E2=80=99s been conse=
rvative when it comes to extracting money from users.
The web3 opportunity. Discord has become the platform-of-choice for web3 en=
tities, but it doesn=E2=80=99t seem to have totally won over hearts and min=
ds. The company needs to capitalize on its lead and protect its positioning=
=2E We have some ideas.=C2=A0
