=9D=C2=A0
A few Redditors trickled in, checked out the product, and spoke with the de=
velopment team via the platform. One reported back, =E2=80=9CI just talked =
to the devs, they=E2=80=99re in there. It=E2=80=99s really cool. Check it o=
ut.=E2=80=9D
That one comment was a miniature inflection point. More users flowed in, an=
d Discord had figured out a grassroots distribution model.=C2=A0
Citron says, =E2=80=9CThat=E2=80=99s the day we say we launched.=E2=80=9D
In the years that followed, Discord succeeded in growing rapidly, accumulat=
ing hundreds of millions of users and close to $1 billion in funding. Perha=
ps more impressively it has managed both to capture gaming culture, and to =
help evangelize it.
#product=C2=A0
Discord was built for gamers, by gamers. While the company has opened its a=
rms to all sorts of new user groups since the beginning of the pandemic, th=
e product retains its gaming speed and verve. As a result, Discord can be a=
 little scary to outsiders.=C2=A0
We like to consider ourselves comfortable with technology; nowhere makes us=
 feel older than a Discord server. To newcomers, it can feel like the Tower=
 of Babel. But slowly, server by server, we=E2=80=99ve learned the language=
, and we=E2=80=99re here to translate for you.=C2=A0
So what is Discord?=C2=A0
Quartz [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE1uxCAMhU8z7BLxExJmwaKbXiMi4C=
RoEkjBaTU9fT2TRSUETzJ-z_68Q1hyedojV2Sva8TnATbBT90AEQo7K5QxBit6aZTu7izYLgijD=
Yt1nAvA7uJmsZzAjnPaoncYc3p3cC41W23np3kaTAj9BE5ypaTpw9zNc09-3Osr150hQvJg4RvK=
Mydgm10Rj3pTHzf5Sefrt_V5J0EeHTcDKb86bNxxNCFWn0toYm3qCiHEtDQRa7O4HUpTcsZK31m=
0kkshBDdCaa1FK9tOAcyem4lmMcL41pe16lDEreP7Itt6ThWdf7yyWbEp45QL2VP5sZL79i7Q6i=
O9-5kiPkdIbtogXFTwgvvmNC6QoBD0MDokpKpXw33Qg1HqokDYOjVwIbRklBwydaX_0D8AVpEV]=
 attempted to capture the multi-faceted magic via analogy mashup: =E2=80=9C=
Picture a combination of Slack, AOL Instant Messenger, Zoom, and a sketchy =
chat room, and you have something approximating Discord.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
PCGamer [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkM-OhCAMxp9muGnknzgHDnvZ1zAIV=
dlBMFDX-PbLjIdNmjb52uZrf9YgLClfek8FyTuNeO2gI5wlACJkchTIo3ea9mzgUjyJ08LRQQ7E=
l3HOAJvxQWM-gOzHFLw16FP8bHQdk2TVT8FA9koNTFGwvWOz6gGAMQ50AjHfvuZwHqIFDb-QrxS=
BBL0i7uXBvx7su8Z5nu1uF7NBbm3aqrIHMAUaiD_papwvNmXXnKsP0HgsTUEfQrOk5Oos8Zp1jF=
LaDZRLKWnLWsEBZtsNkxRVHWxr81qky_Qhum1hbTmmgsa-3nYk65hwStnHpbZfa70jfBr17bHW7=
YgerxGimQK4mwjeYD-MxgUi5ArcjQYrTt5z9VRSDZzfBCoywVVHqWSkOrtUt-K_6R8rJ5Fe] ex=
plained all of the things that Discord lets its users do:
Today Discord lets me do so much, and it's all free:
Talk with as many friends as I want with high audio quality, virtually zero=
 lag, for an unlimited amount of time
Stream games live to anyone in the server with two clicks, also lag free (s=
omehow)
Watch multiple streams at once with individual volume sliders (again, lag f=
ree)
Create virtually unlimited text chat rooms with archives that go back years
Share small-ish files with friends
Bring bots into the mix that can, among many things, broadcast music to eve=
ryone
Oh yea, this all works on phones too, including video streaming and screen =
capture=C2=A0
Discord, though, has a loftier view of itself, one not capturable in analog=
ies or feature lists.
It invites users, current and would-be alike, to imagine a place=E2=80=A6=
=C2=A0
Discord=E2=80=99s first brand marketing campaign invites users, current and=
 would-be alike, to treat its product as a blank canvas on which to project=
 any digital space they can dream up. All types of people are doing just th=
at.=C2=A0
Since the beginning of the pandemic, users of all stripes have flocked to D=
iscord, attracted by its chat features, high-quality audio and video chat, =
privacy, ability to facilitate direct connections, and, unlike Slack, free =
servers.=C2=A0
The company chose to open its arms to non-gamers at just the right time. As=
 every community moved online, they were faced with a choice:=C2=A0
Pay $6.67 per user per month to use the more familiar Slack.=C2=A0
Set up a Discord server and invite unlimited members in for free.=C2=A0
The choice was easy. So easy that people Discord never expected to find in =
a chat tool for gamers knocked down its doors and put down roots.=C2=A0
In 2019, Taylor Lorenz wrote an article [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/e=
JxFkUuOwyAMhk9Tdo14NmTBYjZzjYiAk6BJoAJnotx-3HYxErKNbfSbz8EjLKVe7lkaspcZ8XqC=
y3C2DRChsqNBHVN04iGtMnpg0ekorLEstXGuALtPm8N6AHse05aCx1Ty-wXn0rDVcTBaS8Xt_Ig=
KBh25GXoPHHw_y2mAj64_YoIcwMEv1KtkYJtbEZ_tpr5u8pvOeZ4druBx8xlT6ELZKYsQ1ly2sl=
x08TWs6RcoklwM5Lgis5bzHlMLpcb7CRnvNHJuWMHv95Tn7Xjp1kadxupHLyhgyUkuhRDcCmWME=
Z3stAKYA7eT0ZS1NEBdm4lV3DTfF9m1Y2row89rMFZdLjiVmvJC5Z_V77C9CwRpJL8fOeE1QvbT=
BvHDDz9reBMdF8hQaT1x9Ejw1UP1Q296q9SHFwHWqudCGMlIOZbXp_5F_wBtsJ9K] in The At=
lantic about the influencer invasion of Discord. Instead of letting Faceboo=
k and Twitter=E2=80=99s algorithm-based feeds mediate their relationships w=
ith their fans, influencers began spinning up Discords in droves. According=
 to Forbes [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUc3OpCAQfJrhhuFH1Dl42GTzvY=
ZpoFXyKRjAMfP2284clpBuoENXVZeDikvK7_FIpbI7TPV94BjxKhvWipmdBfMU_Cg7NWjTPpkfW=
y8HM7BQpjkj7hC2seYT2XHaLTioIcXPDyGUYes4t4PQvQJlZ1q9BvTaP11nPYC0IL64cPqA0eGI=
L8zvFJFt41rrUR76z0P90L6uq5lTtlgal3Z6KKFioQw2w25zuiJdlFCCkugo6PvkQ3Epe35B4Yk=
AeF2Rw1Z5DstaC5_hlTJ14m6FyuE4eEwXD1RZiAUnebHUjLBziJ7fvdBz4DQirg23YdtIL3_Bdn=
6U31z1T1kf-q9uvReOdHdWsTASMymlGKQ2xshGNa1GnJ0YrGnpdXCNy2sxPstHK_ZFNeW0pYL7v=
eWyPMZULTGNC5V_V9hx-xRo6hPl_YyhvieMYDf0X0Pq19ePRdOCETP57Seo5KbudP_sTT9o_TWA=
HGt1L6Q0ihGyT7fy_6D_AM18vDw], the article, and Discord=E2=80=99s growing no=
n-gamer user base, surprised Citron and Vishnevskiy.=C2=A0
No strangers to letting user behaviors pull them in new directions, they du=
g in.=C2=A0
When Discord sent out a 23 question survey to its community, they discovere=
d that over 30% of Discord=E2=80=99s users weren=E2=80=99t using the produc=
t primarily for gaming. They were hosting book clubs, friends=E2=80=99 grou=
p chats, fan communities, and even companies. Discord had become the intern=
et=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cthird place.=E2=80=9D As Citron told Patrick O=E2=80=
=99Shaughnessy [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkUtuxCAMhk8TdhPxnJAFi0=
rVXCMi4CS0BCJwWuX2ZWYWlfySLeu3PjuLsOZymSNXJM8w4XWASfBbIyBCIWeFMgVv2J1roeRIv=
JGeaaVJqNNSAHYbosFyAjnOOQZnMeT02qCUK7KZkY_eL-6urGB00F4smno5OqbpqOWs37r29AGS=
AwM_UK6cgESzIR61Ex8dfzT7yiG5HHOtZ-1d3lsLjlCzh9pKpgbJhbi30gUsOd3mM0Qf0nrDDZq=
H4m9HtA468UA7d-ITi03VlXAgCYZTzhijmgmlFOt5LwXA4qielWxd7XpXtqp8YZ2k-8r7es4Vrf=
t-nkKKSRnnXJpcG39vdof4GjQmU8v7mQJeEyQ7R_BvXPim_gI4rZCgtG_4yWJjLe5iGAc1aCHee=
BpPKQbKmOKkKfvcttK_6B8rvpov]:=C2=A0
I read the book, The Great Good Place [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJx=
FkEtuhDAMhk9DlihPyCyyaFVxgnbRFcrDw0QDCUpCET19w7CoZNmyE_u3P6sLTDEdao25oNON5V=
hBBdjzDKVAQluGNHqnSEclE_yGnOKOSCGRz-M9ASzaz6qkDdC6mdlbXXwMrw6MqUAPJUgnCTHAJ=
baml452fc8BS-dcx8HcL129OQ_BgoIfSEcMgGb1KGXNDXtr6FBt3_dWL_o3htbGpRbcWt07xgMl=
38ONn7_YMNYh0fkwNezj63OQDe1MeaaaEeQVxZQQgiVhQgjS0pYzgLvF0gheq9K2Nj2ycIk0HC8=
TbfNmctH2eUqipEIsJqZzOsfPh15gfj3Uy8caly34ctQNtJnBXVDKxfaFaZwgQKrM3ahLJco61t=
960UvGLgiVGmc9JkRQVJVdrF3hX_QPGhOOCg], by Ray Oldenburg, which was written =
in the '80s where he actually talks about this, and starts to put labels an=
d words to describe the concepts of how these third places work. And as I w=
as reading the book, I was just like, "Holy crap, this is what we built, ex=
cept it's digital. This is incredible."
To their credit, Citron and Vishnevskiy, at this point masters of the pivot=
, heard their users and moved swiftly to make all of them feel at home. The=
y evolved the company=E2=80=99s mission=E2=80=A6=C2=A0
=E2=80=A6 and redesigned its brand and homepage.=C2=A0
They launched the =E2=80=9CImagine a Place=E2=80=9D campaign, the company=
=E2=80=99s first ever brand marketing campaign, in May this year, and with =
it, a 6-minute video starring Danny DeVito and Awkwafina:
The video is fast-paced and chaotic and a little confusing... and it captur=
es Discord=E2=80=99s essence perfectly.=C2=A0
